09/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Albanian Customs Director General Shpetim Idrizi and his Italian counterpart, Mario Andrea Guaiana, met on Thursday (8 April) to review co-operation in the fight against trafficking.
The two countries signed an agreement on joint efforts and exchange of information in the field.
Also Thursday, Albania announced plans to launch a programme to rehabilitate juvenile offenders.
The project follows the release of statistics showing an increase in the crime rate among youths.
(ATA, Albanian Radio, Albanian Daily News - 08/04/04)
